# User And Group Management Notes

This file contains quick ad-hoc examples for creating and removing users and groups.

## Create A User

```bash
ansible -i inv remote -b -m user -a "name=test1"
```

## Remove A User

```bash
ansible -i inv remote -b -m user -a "name=test1 state=absent remove=yes"
```

This removes the user and deletes the associated home directory content where supported.

## Create A Group

```bash
ansible -i inv remote -b -m group -a "name=tech"
```

## Add A User To A Group

```bash
ansible -i inv remote -b -m user -a "name=test1 group=tech"
```

## Remove A Group

```bash
ansible -i inv remote -b -m group -a "name=tech state=absent"
```

## Notes

- These commands are useful for quick administration tasks and lab practice.
- In repeatable automation, user and group definitions should usually live in playbooks or dedicated roles.
